INFECTIOUS DISEASES - RUSSIA: 1997
**********************************
A ProMED-mail post
Date: Tue, 27 Jan 1998 14:44:48 +0300 (MSK)
From: N.Shestopalov <shest@gksen.ru>

In 1996 by decree of the President of Russia the functions of the State
Commitee for Sanitary and Epidemiological Surveillance of the Russian
Federation were given to the Ministry of Public Health, and the State
Department for Sanitary and Epidemiological Surveillance of the Russian
Federation was founded in the structure of Ministry for the execution of
those functions.
Now we are glad to inform you that we [are able to] renew sending of
information about the epidemiological situation in Russia to you.
The following information is about some infectious diseases in Russia for
1997.
Diseases: 1997
Number of cases
Salmonellosis (other infections) 60184
Shigellosis 84017
Tuberculosis (new cases) 81100
Including tuberculosis of respiratory tract 65576
Diphtheria 4057
Pertussis 27275
Poliomyelitis 1
Measles 2893
HIV Carriers 3853
AIDS 31
--
Nikolay V.Shestopalov, MD, MPh
Deputy Chief of the Department for Sanitary-and-Epidemiological Surveillance
of the Ministry of Health of the Russian Federation
18/20 Vadkovsky pereulok, Moscow, Russia 101474
Voice/fax: +7 095 978 6805
Email: shest@gksen.ru
[We are pleased to have this renewed official contact. It is striking that
poliomyelitis seems to have been practically eliminated - Mod.JW]
